\": 0.99999998373346, \"rank\": 1.5099859880357008e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The number\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"past decades\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1298}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Buzinski said that when they started tracking the numbers at the Sydney Olympics in 2000, they counted only around five people.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Buzinski\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"the numbers\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sydney Olympics\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"only around five people\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers of the Paris Olympics have underscored diversity and inclusion as major themes, showcasing drag queens and refugee athletes in Friday's opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"major themes\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"refugee athletes\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday's opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That has received some blowback from religious conservatives.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some blowback\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"religious conservatives\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In our Olympic world, we all belong,\\\"Thomas Bach, International Olympic Committee president said in a speech during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1708, \"end\": 1739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our Olympic world\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"a speech\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1766}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of that and Paris' reputation as the \\\"City of Love,\\\" Buzinski and LGBTQ+ advocates see the Paris Games as an opportunity for athletes who hail from parts of the world where competitors can not be openly gay because of harsh restrictions on queer populations.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 2063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998258318, \"rank\": 1.7426346089682742e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the \\\"City\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"Love\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"Buzinski and LGBTQ+ advocates\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1907}, {\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"parts\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1958}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"harsh restrictions\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2041}, {\"ngram\": \"queer populations\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Coming to Paris, coming to France, they are able to be their true selves,\\\" said J\\u00e9r\\u00e9my Goupille, co-chair of the Pride House at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2076, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998258318, \"rank\": 1.7426346089682742e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2093, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9990297576075938, \"rank\": 0.0004982963154054239, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_House\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pride House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_House\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their true selves\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"J\\u00e9r\\u00e9my Goupille\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2161}, {\"ngram\": \"co\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2165}, {\"ngram\": \"chair\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Pride House, which debuted at the 2010 Olympics, is located on a boat floating on the Seine River and will feature live music and speeches from Olympic organizers as it opens Monday night.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_(comics)\", \"score\": 0.666814709508023, \"rank\": 0.4686248331107615, \"text\": \"The Pride\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_(comics)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_(comics)\"}, {\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_House\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pride House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pride_House\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2010 Olympics\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"a boat\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"live music\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"speeches\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2357}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic organizers\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Goupille said security concerns still remain for many athletes.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Goupille\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2417}, {\"ngram\": \"security concerns\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2440}, {\"ngram\": \"many athletes\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dating apps like Grindr, Bumble and Tinder have long been used as a shield for gay athletes who want to connect with other queer people in the countries where they are competing but do not want to feel publicly exposed.\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grindr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grindr\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grindr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grindr\"}, {\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bumble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.4383038425833036e-24, \"text\": \"Bumble\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bumble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bumble\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dating apps\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2484}, {\"ngram\": \"Tinder\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"a shield\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"gay athletes\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"other queer people\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"the countries\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he said in previous Games, some have tried to expose athletes that are not officially out by checking heights, weights and locations of people on those apps.\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"previous Games\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"heights\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"weights\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"locations\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2830}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2840}, {\"ngram\": \"those apps\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of that, Grindr announced that in Paris they have disabled location-based features within the Olympic village where athletes stay and other official Games areas, saying it would allow LGBTQ+ athletes to connect \\\"authentically without worrying about prying eyes or unwanted attention.\\\"\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 3149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2874, \"end\": 2880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grindr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grindr\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.o